==What is OrgOddmuse ?==
OrgOddmuse is a mode that transforms OrgMode text to OddmuseWiki format (see TextFormattingRules).

==Install==
: Put Lisp:org-oddmuse.el in your load-path, add
{{{
    (require 'org-oddmuse)
}}}    
: in ~/.emacs

==Usage==
* `org-oddmuse-transform-subtree'
  Transforms Org-mode subtree to Oddmuse Wiki format.
* `org-oddmuse-transform-current-buffer'
  Transforms current Org-mode buffer to Oddmuse Wiki format.
* `org-oddmuse-transform-buffer'
  Transforms buffer to Oddmuse Wiki format.

==Customize==
You can customize the option below by: M-x customize-group RET org-oddmuse RET

* `org-oddmuse-transform-level'
: The level of transform heading.
: If it is nil, it will transform all Org-mode headings with Oddmuse Wiki format.
: If it is a number, it just transforms heading to the specified level (index from 1).
